pped and melee are not?  Do you believe that casters only need 1/2 the AC that melee do (considering 500-600 of AC is avoidance from defense skill) to max out their effectiveness against exp mobs?<br><br>How do you explain that casters get no benefit from AC over 900 vs exp mobs but melee get benefit up to 1200 AC vs exp mobs if there is no AC cap? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugaryen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Garyen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.houseofdarklight.netfirms.com/other/g.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Representing the Half-Elf</BR>Guardian of the Arena</BR>STEEL WARRIOR Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 1183<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/15/02 1:43:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1919.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/classes/c_warrior.gif width=71 height=177></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I have a question for those who dont believe in an AC ca</span><hr size=1> There are still people who don't believe in the AC cap? <p><p align="left"><b>-garyen varillious al'dar<br>-representing the half elf<br>-60th warlord of rodcet nife<br>-steel warrior of freeport</b><br><br><img src="http://www.houseofdarklight.netfirms.com/GARISABEAST.jpg" border="0"</p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubonehammer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bonehammer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/15/02 2:22:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1919.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I have a question for those who dont believe in an AC ca</span><hr size=1> I like your question, but your argument is still based on something that is more believed than proven.<br><br>Casters capped at 900 AC?  Gotta prove it.  Them saying they noticed no improvement between overnuking and dying means zip.<br><br>Warriors capped at 1250 AC?  I haven't read much to sway me either way.  Popular opinion means jack vs reality.  I want to believe it, simply because I have thrown many great AC items in the bank for more HPs.  Can I prove it?  Nope.  Would love to hear from someone who can.  Simply noticing no significant difference is meaningless. <p><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=9666 ">Bonehammer</a><BR>Warlord of Phantom Raiders<BR><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=171833 ">Fisc</a><BR>High Priest of Phantom Raiders<BR>Bertoxxulous</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usolinarinnoruuk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Solinar Innoruuk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 160<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/15/02 2:56:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1919.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I have a question for those who dont believe in an AC ca</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Casters capped at 900 AC? Gotta prove it. Them saying they noticed no improvement between overnuking and dying means zip.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>There was some pretty extensive tests done by an enchanter with 800-850-900-950-1000AC in early velious on the mist panther in WL.<br><br>He had a pretty large sample size, and it showed that 800 AC was good, 850 was a significant reduction, 900 was a little better, 950 was exactly the same as 900, and 1000 was exactly the same as 1000. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugrimmlokk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimmlokk</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://grimmlokk.homestead.com/files/icon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 852<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/15/02 4:32:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1919.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://grimmlokk.homestead.com/files/spinhead2.gif?flezbwidth=30&flezbheight=41? WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I have a question for those who dont believe in an AC ca</span><hr size=1>  Would it be that hard to believe casters AC is capped lower? I know in Denzalo's one post he claimed monk cap was 1100ish while plate were 1200. Would make sense for casters to be lower if that's true. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugraalthedorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Graal the Dorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/15/02 5:45:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1919.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I have a question for those who dont believe in an AC ca</span><hr size=1> Let's think about this for a bit. There is a supposed cap on AC whereby adding more AC does not reduce the average damage per hit. That's mitigation.<br><br>AC is a composite number. Saying that there is a softcap at 1250 AC doesn't take into account the fact that about half of that AC is avoidance AC.<br><br>Let's assume there is a softcap to AC at 1250 AC for a plate class tank. If you compare the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> avoidance</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> AC of the tank to a pure caster, you will see that the pure caster has about 224 avoidance AC less than the melee, and probably closer to 250-300 less, depending on AGI. <br><br>1250 composite AC - 250 avoidance AC difference between casters and plate classes = 1000 composite AC. A pure caster with 1000 total AC will have roughly the same mitigation AC as a plate class with about 1250 AC.<br><br>If you are going to try and talk about a softcap to mitigation AC, you really, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> really</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> need to seperate out the avoidance and mitigation portions of AC. <p><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14686"> Graal MacBladefury</A><BR>Crusader of Brell<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uroenae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Roenae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/15/02 8:13:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1919.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I have a question for those who dont believe in an AC ca</span><hr size=1> Please... lookup the research that has been put into the Stats/skils FAQ(hit the back button then look at the top of the page <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . there is an excellent section there on the AC softcap.<br><br>It might take a while to read... but do it! <p><center><img src="http://www.warlocksdomain.com/.sig/Roenae_sig.jpg" border="0"><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=304840" target=top>Magelo Character Profile</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=thoric>Thoric</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/15/02 8:36:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1919.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I have a question for those who dont believe in an AC ca</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Warriors capped at 1250 AC? I haven't read much to sway me either way. Popular opinion means jack vs reality. I want to believe it, simply because I have thrown many great AC items in the bank for more HPs. Can I prove it? Nope. Would love to hear from someone who can. Simply noticing no significant difference is meaningless.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Probably because you haven't done a search on this topic on this very forum.  It was discussed extensively and I believe it was Gorlab of KotF who first brought it to warriors' attention over at Stratics.  He did extensive testing on Lord Yelinak and NToV dragons with AC ranging from 1550 to 1050? (memory of exact details getting faint) in 100AC increment and keeping agi constant to rule out avoidance variables.  If that's not good enough, then do your own test. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uarlinastarbright.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arlina Starbright</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/15/02 11:04:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1919.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I have a question for those who dont believe in an AC ca</span><hr size=1> I <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> have</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> searched the topic on this forum, and while I can find everybody and their brother claiming that tests have been done that have proven the soft cap, the only actual uber mob test I could find was linked by someone <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> else</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> who had spent a ton of time searching several different forums, and that was a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> small</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> vindicator test.<br><br>The only other logs I have seen are mist panther logs and enchanter vs exp mob logs. (which popped up on the enchanter forums on CR)<br><br>Arlina <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/unooneofnote.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NoOneOfNote</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/15/02 11:20:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1919.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   AC cap</span><hr size=1> <br>There may well be an AC cap, lots of things in the game are capped.<br><br>However the calculation on mob damage also proved the graph of mitigation armor versus damage is not constant. There will exist &quot;too low&quot; and &quot;too high&quot; zones where changing armor will have zero effect. You can see a stupid example of this if you get 1300 AC and tank an orc pawn in the commons. Add plus or minus 500 AC and the orc pawn will still hit for minimum or be mitigated to a miss.  It also moves in increments so small changes may have zero effect.<br><br>It is possible 1300 AC is too high for Velious mobs and too low for luclin boss mobs. Or it may just be capped there. In practice it doesn't really matter until someone finds an AC number which reduces damage against a current high end boss. Until then 1300 AC acts as a point of diminishing returns even if it isn't an actual cap. Net result more or less the same.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugrimmlokk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimmlokk</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://grimmlokk.homestead.com/files/icon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 853<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/16/02 2:17:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1919.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://grimmlokk.homestead.com/files/spinhead2.gif?flezbwidth=30&flezbheight=41? WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC cap</span><hr size=1> &quot;It was discussed extensively and I believe it was Gorlab of KotF who first brought it to warriors' attention over at Stratics. He did extensive testing on Lord Yelinak and NToV dragons with AC ranging from 1550 to 1050? (memory of exact details getting faint) in 100AC increment and keeping agi constant to rule out avoidance variables. If that's not good enough, then do your own test.&quot;<br><br> The reason memory of exact details are faint is exact details were never posted =P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uarlinastarbright.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arlina Starbright</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/16/02 5:58:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1919.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC cap</span><hr size=1> 1300 as a point of diminishing returns?<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  700</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> is a point of diminishing returns vs exp mobs (e.g. krup knight, crystalline watcher, tae ew warrior).<br><br>AC changes in that range still make fairly sizable differences, but 600-700 will still make more of a difference than 700-800.<br><br>Arlina <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uarlinastarbright.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arlina Starbright</A> at: 8/16/02 6:00:31 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utamria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tamria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 135<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/16/02 6:02:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1919.topic&index=12>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC cap</span><hr size=1> Firstly your subject line is flawed. The questino is not whether there is an AC softcap but whether or not mob ATTK plays a part in determining it.<br><br>The chanter that did the mist panther testing needs to do the same test on other lvl 60 mobs (like a trash drake in ToV). If across all those mobs the softcap is still 900ac  then it would appear that indeed the softcap is not affected by mob ac. However if against say the ToV drake he finds the cap to be 1200 ac then the only thing has changed is the mob - one logical conclusion to draw from that is the mob ATTk values are different and that is affecting the equation.<br><br>Of course the fact there are two types of AC and that these may be weighted differently in calculations further complicates things. Even if against all mobs it appeared the chanter softcapped at 900ac it wouldn't prove that mob ATTK had no influence because the chanter is only adding one type of AC. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubonehammer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bonehammer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/16/02 7:54:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1919.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC cap</span><hr size=1> Insult my intelligence if you like when I ask for proof.  Spend some time browsing the AC cap in the Q&amp;A and you will find 20 intelligent folks all drawing different conclusions from the same posted (or unposted) data.  <br><br>Some spend their time gathering the data however they see fit.<br>Some spend it discounting the test or the tester.<br>Some attack the poor choice of mob, because it wasn't uber enough, including the caster AC test mob in WL.<br>Some throw their hands up at missing posts.<br>Some quote something they heard or assume.<br>Some re-evaluate the data and conclude different from the tester.<br><br>It must not be safe to come here and discuss, lest you be drawn and quartered for your search for the truth.  I think it would be better not to sheep around and go with what is popular opinion.  The same opinion that believed AC was the ultimate stat not so long ago.<br><br><br>There are some great posts to be read, although they do seem upsetting.  What to do?  Follow Aeryl Firebrand some and you find that, depending on the mob, AC between 1145 and 1600 makes no difference for your typical blue mob.  Changes in ATK rating for raid level mobs bring that minimum number up to what? 1250?  Okay.  How about the folks of similar stature that dont agree?  I'm not waiting around for someone to tell me 'how it works' before I make gear selections.  I am geared for how the mobs are tanked 'today' from our own trial and error.<br><br>The game seems to sort itself out, and how many times have we seen a new path appear?  Where is it going next... <p><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=9666 ">Bonehammer</a><BR>Warlord of Phantom Raiders<BR><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=171833 ">Fisc</a><BR>High Priest of Phantom Raiders<BR>Bertoxxulous</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utenakha.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tenakha</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 443<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/16/02 7:57:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1919.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC cap</span><hr size=1> &gt;The reason memory of exact details are faint is exact details <br>&gt;were never posted =P <br><br>I posted my test results on stratics. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7197 style="text-decoration: none">Gorlab</a> 60 Warlord<BR>Tenakha 53 Druid<BR>Officer of <a href=http://www.keepersof